I"l<p>Piotr Wozniak argues that good learning is inherently pleasurable. He argues that people have <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/biological-reward-systems-are-malleable">an innate drive for learning</a>, innately associated with reward systems. This is consonant with the view of the human as an infovore, wired from birth to accumulate knowledge.</p>
